# Per-drawing binary artifacts are NOT committed: the source drawings are public OEM
# literature (copyright retained by the publisher) and would bloat the repo. The immutable
# TEXT evidence for each test IS committed as a sanitized artifact:
#   source.json, sha256.txt, telegram_request.json, telegram_response.{txt,json},
#   extraction.json, judge_1.json, report.md, report.html, run.log, index.{json,md}.
original.*
tested_page.png
*.pdf
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.webp
*.tif
_email/
_runner.sqlite

# run.log is intentional per-drawing evidence — re-include it despite the repo-root `*.log` ignore.
!run.log
